ize>192</BitSize><SubItem><Name>uuidEventClass</Name><Type GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000021}">GUID</Type><BitSize>128</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>nEventId</Name><Type GUID="{18071995-0000-0000-0000-000000000008}">UDINT</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>128</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>eSeverity</Name><Type GUID="{B57D3F4A-0836-49B0-81C3-BED5F4817EC9}">TcEventSeverity</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>160</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>eFlags</Name><Type GUID="{EB67FE92-FBB1-4149-A2D5-DDFE2EFA568C}">TcEventEntryFlags</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>176</BitOffs></SubItem><Hides><Hide GUID="{F00C83AD-DEC8-486E-AE99-5E0A75C26DE0}" /><Hide GUID="{128902B7-F178-4299-B8BF-51215A80685F}" /></Hides></DataType><DataType><Name>UDINT (81..10000)</Name><BitSize>32</BitSize><BaseType>UDINT</BaseType><Properties><Property><Name>LowerBorder</Name><Value>81</Value></Property><Property><Name>UpperBorder</Name><Value>10000</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>ST_SensorData</Name><Comment><![CDATA[
============================================================
ST_SensorData
============================================================
PURPOSE
  Holds all sensor readings converted to engineering units.
  Populated by FB_SensorIO every PLC cycle.
  Consumed by MAIN, FB_CSVLogger, and FB_MqttManager.

WATER LEVEL
  Three sensors: L1V11 (primary), L1V20 (secondary), L2V21 (tertiary).
  rWaterLevel_pct  — percentage 0–100 % (primary sensor only).
  rWaterLevel_mm   — absolute level in mm (primary sensor only).

TEMPERATURE
  Two channels from EL3202 RTD card.
  rTemperature_C[1] — Probe 1 in degrees Celsius.
  rTemperature_C[2] — Probe 2 in degrees Celsius.

POSITION FEEDBACK (encoder)
  Raw encoder counts scaled to mm for each valve axis.
  rPosFeedback_mm[1..3] — supplementary position, not used by MC2
  (MC2 reads encoder directly via NC axis).

FAULT FLAGS
  bWaterLevelFault — raw value below disconnection threshold.
  bTempFault[1..2] — raw value below disconnection threshold.
============================================================
]]></Comment><BitSize>416</BitSize><SubItem><Name>rWaterLevel_pct</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Primary sensor: 0–100 %           ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rWaterLevel_mm</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Primary sensor: 0–ENG_MAX mm      ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rWaterLevel_raw</Name><Type>INT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Raw ADC value for diagnostics      ]]></Comment><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bWaterLevelFault</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE if sensor disconnected/out-rng]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>80</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rTemperature_C</Name><Type>REAL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>2</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ Probe 1 and 2 in °C           ]]></Comment><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>96</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rTemperature_raw</Name><Type>INT</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>2</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ Raw ADC values for diagnostics ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>160</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bTempFault</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>2</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE if sensor fault           ]]></Comment><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>192</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rPosFeedback_mm</Name><Type>REAL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>3</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ Encoder position in mm         ]]></Comment><BitSize>96</BitSize><BitOffs>224</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rPosFeedback_raw</Name><Type>INT</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>3</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ Raw counts for diagnostics     ]]></Comment><BitSize>48</BitSize><BitOffs>320</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bPosFeedbackFault</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>3</Elements></ArrayInfo><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE if encoder disconnected   ]]></Comment><BitSize>24</BitSize><BitOffs>368</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bAnySensorFault</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ OR of all fault flags              ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>392</BitOffs></SubItem></DataType><DataType><Name>FB_SensorIO</Name><Comment><![CDATA[
============================================================
FUNCTION_BLOCK: FB_SensorIO
============================================================

PURPOSE
  Reads raw analog INT values from GVL_IO (EL3074 / EL3202),
  scales them to engineering units, applies a low-pass filter
  for noise rejection, detects sensor faults, and outputs
  a fully populated ST_SensorData struct.

  Call this block once per PLC cycle in MAIN before any
  other FB that consumes sensor data.

INPUTS
  bEnable         — Master enable; when FALSE outputs hold
                    last valid value and bAnySensorFault = TRUE.
  rLpfAlpha       — Low-pass filter coefficient (0.0–1.0).
                    0.0 = no filtering (pass-through).
                    0.9 = heavy filtering (slow to respond).
                    Default 0.1 gives moderate noise rejection.

OUTPUTS
  stOut           — Fully populated ST_SensorData struct.

WATER LEVEL SCALING
  Linear mapping: (raw − RAW_MIN) / (RAW_MAX − RAW_MIN) × ENG_RANGE
  Scaling constants defined in GVL_Config.

TEMPERATURE SCALING
  EL3202 RTD card outputs tenths of a degree Celsius as INT.
  e.g. raw = 250 → 250 × 0.1 + OFFSET = 25.0 °C

FAULT DETECTION
  Any raw value ≤ GVL_Config.SENSOR_FAULT_THRESHOLD is treated
  as a disconnected or failed sensor (default threshold = -100;
  unconnected GVL_IO stubs initialize to -999).

HARDWARE MAPPING (GVL_IO)
  Water level:   AI_L1V11 (primary), AI_L1V20, AI_L2V21
  Temperature:   AI_Tmp_1, AI_Tmp_2  (EL3202 PT100)
  Position FB:   AI_PosFeedback_1/2/3 (supplementary only)

LIBRARIES
  Tc2_Standard
============================================================
]]></Comment><BitSize>960</BitSize><SubItem><Name>bEnable</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Master enable; FALSE holds last value ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs><Default><Bool>true</Bool></Default><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rLpfAlpha</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Low-pass filter: 0.0=off, 0.9=heavy   ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>96</BitOffs><Default><Value>0.1</Value></Default><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>stOut</Name><Type>ST_SensorData</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ All sensor readings in engineering units ]]></Comment><BitSize>416</BitSize><BitOffs>128</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rFilt_WaterLevel</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ ── Low-pass filter state variables ─────────────────────── ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>544</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rFilt_Temp1</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>576</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rFilt_Temp2</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>608</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rFilt_PosFb</Name><Type>REAL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>3</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>96</BitSize><BitOffs>640</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rRaw_WaterLevel_mm</Name><Type>REAL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ ── Scaled (pre-filter) intermediate values ──────────────── ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>736</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rRaw_Temp1_C</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>768</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rRaw_Temp2_C</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>800</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rRaw_PosFb_mm</Name><Type>REAL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Elements>3</Elements></ArrayInfo><BitSize>96</BitSize><BitOffs>832</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bFirstScan</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ ── First-scan flag (initialise filters from first reading) ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>928</BitOffs><Default><Bool>true</Bool></Default></SubItem><SubItem><Name>i</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>944</BitOffs></SubItem><Method><Name>ScaleLinear</Name><Comment><![CDATA[
============================================================
METHOD: ScaleLinear
============================================================
PURPOSE
  Maps a raw value from [rawMin, rawMax] to [engMin, engMax]
  using linear interpolation.

  result = engMin + (raw - rawMin) / (rawMax - rawMin) * (engMax - engMin)

  If rawMax = rawMin the method returns engMin to avoid
  division by zero.
============================================================
]]></Comment><ReturnType>REAL</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>rRaw</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>rRawMin</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>rRawMax</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>rEngMin</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>rEngMax</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter></Method><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Tc2_System">T_MaxString</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ TwinCAT PLC string of max. length of 255 bytes + 1 byte null delimiter. ]]></Comment><BitSize>2048</BitSize><BaseType>STRING(255)</BaseType></DataType><DataType><Name>E_ValveSource</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>NONE</Text><Enum>0</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ No command received yet (startup default)]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>HMI</Text><Enum>1</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Last setpoint was entered via local HMI]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>MQTT</Text><Enum>2</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Last setpoint was received via MQTT topic]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>generate_implicit_init_function</Name></Property><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property><Property><Name>strict</Name></Property><Property><Name>to_string</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>E_ValveState</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>INIT</Text><Enum>0</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Initializing, powering axis]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>HOMING</Text><Enum>1</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Performing homing sequence (MC_Home)]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>IDLE</Text><Enum>2</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ At position, no active command]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>MOVING</Text><Enum>3</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ MC_MoveA