============================================================
ST_MQTT_Command
============================================================
PURPOSE
  JSON-deserialized incoming MQTT command payload.
  FB_MqttManager parses received JSON into this struct.

EXPECTED JSON FORMAT (publish to irrigation/command):
  {
    "Valve1": 50,
    "Valve2": 25,
    "Valve3": 75,
    "Valve1_Enable": true,
    "Valve2_Enable": true,
    "Valve3_Enable": false
  }

  Valve setpoints are in percent (0–100).
  ValveN_Enable = true  → MQTT is allowed to command that valve.
  ValveN_Enable = false → that valve ignores MQTT setpoints.
  Omitting a field leaves its current value unchanged.

NOTES
  • {attribute 'TcJsonObject'} enables Beckhoff JSON auto-parse.
  • DINT used for setpoints to avoid floating-point JSON quirks;
    values are clamped to 0–100 before use.
============================================================
]]></Comment><BitSize>128</BitSize><SubItem><Name>Valve1</Name><Type>DINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Desired position valve 1, 0–100 % ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Valve2</Name><Type>DINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Desired position valve 2, 0–100 % ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>32</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Valve3</Name><Type>DINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Desired position valve 3, 0–100 % ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Valve1_Enable</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE = allow MQTT to command valve 1 ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>96</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Valve2_Enable</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE = allow MQTT to command valve 2 ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>104</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Valve3_Enable</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE = allow MQTT to command valve 3 ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>112</BitOffs></SubItem><Properties><Property><Name>TcJsonObject</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name>FB_MqttManager</Name><Comment><![CDATA[
============================================================
FUNCTION_BLOCK: FB_MqttManager
============================================================

PURPOSE
  Central MQTT manager for the irrigation system.
  Handles connection lifecycle, topic subscription, cyclic
  status publishing, and incoming JSON command parsing.

CONNECTION STATE MACHINE
  DISABLED     — bEnable = FALSE; waiting to be enabled
  CONNECTING   — Applying config and requesting connection
  CONNECTED    — Active; monitoring for loss or config change
  DISCONNECTING— Gracefully closing connection
  WAIT_RECONNECT— Back-off delay before retry

OUTGOING JSON (published to stConfig.sMainTopic):
  {
    "timestamp": "2026-04-28 12:00:00",
    "valve_1_setpoint": 50.0, "valve_1_actual": 49.8, "valve_1_source": "HMI",
    "valve_2_setpoint": 25.0, "valve_2_actual": 25.1, "valve_2_source": "MQTT",
    "valve_3_setpoint": 75.0, "valve_3_actual": 74.9, "valve_3_source": "HMI",
    "temperature_c": 22.5,
    "water_level_pct": 65.3,
    "water_level_mm": 653.0
  }

INCOMING JSON (subscribed from stConfig.SubscribeTopic):
  {
    "Valve1": 50, "Valve2": 25, "Valve3": 75,
    "Valve1_Enable": true, "Valve2_Enable": true, "Valve3_Enable": false
  }
  Setpoints are in % (0-100). ValveN_Enable gates MQTT override.
  Deserialized into ST_MQTT_Command via Beckhoff JSON parser.

AUTO-SUBSCRIBE
  On every new connection (CONNECTED state), the FB automatically
  subscribes to stConfig.SubscribeTopic. No external trigger needed.

LIBRARIES
  TF6701 / Tc3_IotBase, Tc3_JsonXml, Tc2_Standard
============================================================
]]></Comment><BitSize>127744</BitSize><SubItem><Name>bEnable</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Master enable; FALSE disconnects MQTT     ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>stConfig</Name><Type>ST_MqttConfig</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Broker address, port, username, topics    ]]></Comment><BitSize>6336</BitSize><BitOffs>96</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bApplyConfig</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Rising edge: reconnect with new config    ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>6432</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bPublish</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Rising edge: publish current status JSON  ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>6440</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>bEnableStatusPublish</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE = publish status JSON cyclically     ]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>6448</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>tStatusPublishTime</Name><Type>TIME</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Interval, e.g. T#5M                       ]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>6464</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>sStatusTopic</Name><Type>STRING(255)</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Publish topic, e.g. 'irrigation/status'  ]]></Comment><BitSize>2048</BitSize><BitOffs>6496</BitOffs><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Input</Value></Property></Properties></SubItem><SubItem><Name>rValveSetpoint</Name><Type>REAL</Type><ArrayInfo><LBound>1</LBound><Eleme