============================================================
PROGRAM: MAIN
============================================================

PURPOSE
  Top-level program that orchestrates all function blocks
  and manages the system data bus between GVLs.

EXECUTION ORDER (every PLC cycle)
  1. Initialise MQTT config from defaults (first scan only)
  2. Copy HMI inputs to GVL_System bus
  3. FB_SensorIO      — Read and scale analog sensor inputs
  4. FB_ValveControl  — Per-valve TC2_MC2 state machines (x3)
  5. Build timestamp string for MQTT and logging
  6. FB_MqttManager   — MQTT connection, publish, subscribe
  7. FB_CsvLogger     — Periodic CSV row logging
  8. Mirror runtime data to GVL_HMI for display
  9. Compute system health flags

DATA FLOW
  GVL_IO  --> FB_SensorIO --> GVL_System.Sensors
  GVL_HMI.HMI_* --> GVL_System.Valve[n] setpoints
  FB_MqttManager.rMqttValveSetpoint --> FB_ValveControl MQTT_Setpoint
  FB_ValveControl outputs --> GVL_System.Valve[n] status
  GVL_System.* --> GVL_HMI.ACT_* (for display)
  GVL_System.Valve + Sensors --> FB_MqttManager (outgoing JSON)
  GVL_System.Valve + Sensors --> FB_CsvLogger (CSV row)

LIBRARIES
  TC2_MC2, TF6701 / Tc3_IotBase, Tc2_System
============================================================
]]></Comment><SubItem><Name Static="true">bMqttConfigInit</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ ── First-scan flag for MQTT default config load ─────────────]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><Default><Bool>false</Bool></Default></SubItem><SubItem><Name Static="true">fbSensorIO</Name><Type>FB_SensorIO</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ ── Function block instances ────────────────────────────────]]></Comment><BitSize>960</BitSize></SubItem><SubItem><Name Static="true">fbCsvLogger</Name><Type>FB_CsvLogger</Type><BitSize>54912</BitSize></SubItem><SubItem><Name Static="true">fbMqttManager</Name><Type>FB_MqttManager</Type><BitSize>127744</BitSize></SubItem><SubItem><Name Static="true">Axis_Valve1</Name><Type Namespace="Tc2_MC2">AXIS_REF</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ ── NC Axis references ──────────────────────────────────────
